<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Lorenna from Atlantic:
[B]I have a scroll vendot I keep stocked. I have a bag for each level of scroll and try to keep at least one of each on the vendor at all times. I sell bulk packs of recalls and gates and try to keep several of each of the level 8's avialable. I price as above and sell out regualarly. I do find my best friend is dear Walter - he's steady sort and never talks back to me!! Runebooks are a hot seller, easy to make and a good source of money. Be sure to provide runes back to your shop cheaply. 

Stocking all scrolls is highly appreciated by loyal customers. I'd do it, though I know busy vendors that have recalls, gates, all level 8's and runebooks and seem to do very well.[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
