<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum114/HTML/000064.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#000000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#5C0000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">ImaMula - Atlantic</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">What scrolls would you sell? Recall? Gate? Mark? Any others?  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/confused.gif"> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">lordwu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I think recall/mark/gate sell the best. I'm starting a scribe lately and already sold like 80 recall scrolls in 2 days. But I think the best vendor is having scrolls in all circles in stock. Maybe 1 or 2 scrolls for less popular scrolls and larger amount for recall/mark/gate/res.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Vanin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Recalls/Gates/Marks are by far the most popular.  All the 8th circle summon scrolls go quick too at a fair price.  I have mine set up with individual scroll bags for 4th - 8th circle.  I also maintain seprate bags for recalls, gates, marks, and res scrolls.  This seems to work really well for me.  The reason the lower circles aren't mainained anymore is they are fairly common to find.  Leave a book on the floor for orders or on the vendor with a email address.  One thing I strongly recommend, once your doing eighth, if you place all circles of scrolls on a vendor, if you sell full spellbooks make sure the cost for one of each scroll your selling adds up to the cost of the book.  Reason being is you'll spend more time making 1st through 6th scrolls and the spellbooks sit. Not to mention there's no profit in the lower circle spells  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Vanin, GM Scribe<BR>BlackRose TR, Pacific Shard</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Boucka</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">The same for LS.  Recalls/Gates/Marks sell very well. Runebooks work well too. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">lordwu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I agree that low circle scrolls don't make money. I would rather see it as a service to the customers. Customers will know they can find *Anything* on your vendor and they will keep coming back. Some people would prefer to pay a little more rather than running around collecting scrolls.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Archie</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I am in total agreeance with lordwu. I have a scroll vendor at each of my shops. They do quite well and my customers know that what ever they need, they will find there. My vendors carry one of each scroll in individual boxes and extra individual scrolls and bulk packs of recall, mark, gate and resurrection. I buy all my level 1 - 3 scrolls from the mage shops. I charge 25, 35, 45, 55, 65, 75, 100 and 200 respectively. I also carry a full spellbook for 4k and have a hard time keeping them in stock. If prices seem high, sometimes you have to pay more for convenience. That is where all your mini marts come from. This is a very popular vendor. <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>No good deed goes unpunished.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Lorenna from Atlantic</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I have a scroll vendot I keep stocked. I have a bag for each level of scroll and try to keep at least one of each on the vendor at all times. I sell bulk packs of recalls and gates and try to keep several of each of the level 8's avialable. I price as above and sell out regualarly. I do find my best friend is dear Walter - he's steady sort and never talks back to me!! Runebooks are a hot seller, easy to make and a good source of money. Be sure to provide runes back to your shop cheaply. <P>Stocking all scrolls is highly appreciated by loyal customers. I'd do it, though I know busy vendors that have recalls, gates, all level 8's and runebooks and seem to do very well.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
